column1: I'll use general marine suggestions for your area.
ecosystems have unique characteristics that I'll consider in my suggestions.

elements, but I couldn't generate connections between them.

Excellent work! You've completed your DAPSI(W)R(M) model with connections. Review the summary on the right, and when ready, click 'Save to ISA Data Entry' to transfer your model to the main ISA module.
Model saved! Navigate to 'ISA Data Entry' to see your elements.
Your work is already saved automatically. Navigate to 'ISA Data Entry' to see your elements.
Navigate to 'ISA Data Entry' and complete your SES model
Go to 'CLD Visualization' and click 'Generate CLD'
Google's algorithm: importance based on quality and quantity of incoming connections.
PageRank: Google's algorithm adapted for network analysis. Measures overall importance considering both direct connections and the importance of connecting nodes.
High Eigenvector: Target nodes that are influential because they're connected to other influential nodes.
Skip if you're not sure or want to see all options
Skip if multiple needs apply or you're unsure
Select the human activities relevant to your marine management question. These represent the 'Drivers' and 'Activities' in the DAPSI(W)R(M) framework.
Select the environmental pressures, risks, or hazards you're concerned about. These represent 'Pressures' and 'State changes' in the DAPSI(W)R(M) framework.
List key impacts on human welfare you've observed...
Select a template and click 'Review' to preview connections
Or click 'Load' to load it as-is without review
